description: Impossible Engineering: Series 4 Technology Documentary hosted by Mike Bratton, published by Discovery Channel broadcasted as part of Science Ch. series in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/9/91/Impossible-Engineering-Series-4-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Impossible Engineering: Series 4 Behind every seemingly-impossible marvel of modern engineering is a cast of heroic trailblazers who pioneered new building techniques. As we revel in these modern day creations we leap back in time to recount the stories of the exceptional engineers behind the historic technological advances that made it all possible. 8) Inside the Tesla Factory The Tesla car factory is one of the largest and most innovative factories in the world. This state-of-the-art facility is the home to high-tech robots that work around-the-clock to produce thousands of cutting-edge electric cars each week.
